Project: snowcast
Author: Quan Fang
Email: fangquans@gmail.com

The structure of my program:
Step 1, Set up socket for TCP
Step 2, Set up socket for UDP, bind the UDP socket with localhost and udpport
Step 3, Find the Internet address of the server and connect TCP to the server
Step 4, send HELLO and receive WELCOME, setting handshake
Step 5, 
while (1) {
	if (stdin) {
		user interaction;
	}
	if (tcpsocket) {
		receive server announcement and invalid command feedback
	}
	if (udpsocket) {
		receive music data
	}
}


Usage:
Running the server:
	cs033_snowcast_server port /course/cs033/pub/snowcast/*
Running the client:
	./snowcast_client servername serverport udpport 2032 | mpg123 -



